            "content": "# Tool-Failure Retry Cap Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Resolve PR #2065 review feedback by adding a `consecutive_all_failed` counter that caps retries, re-wires the dead `tool_failure` notification event, and locks the retry-on-failure contract in with regression tests.\n\n**Architecture:** Track a per-loop `consecutive_all_failed_iterations: u32` counter in both streaming and non-streaming agent loops in `agent_loop.rs`. Increment when every tool in an iteration failed (non-soft errors); reset on any success. At cap (3), exit with a new `LibreFangError::RepeatedToolFailures` error. The kernel's `send_message` Err handler maps that variant to `push_notification(agent_id, \"tool_failure\", ...)`, restoring the previously-dead notification semantic. Regression tests use mock `LlmDriver` impls (pattern: existing `EmptyAfterToolUseDriver`) to verify (a) retry happens after a single failure and (b) cap-exit happens after 3 consecutive all-failed iterations.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust, tokio, thiserror, async_trait.\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n- `crates/librefang-types/src/error.rs` — add `RepeatedToolFailures { iterations, error_count }` variant.\n- `crates/librefang-runtime/src/agent_loop.rs` — add counter + cap logic in both `run_agent_loop` (~line 1570) and `run_agent_loop_streaming` (~line 3078); add mock drivers + regression tests.\n- `crates/librefang-kernel/src/kernel.rs` — map `RepeatedToolFailures` → `push_notification(\"tool_failure\", ...)` in the `send_message` Err handler (~line 3297).\n\nConstants already defined in `agent_loop.rs`:\n- `MAX_ITERATIONS: u32 = 50` (line 38)\n\nNew constant:\n- `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_ALL_FAILED: u32 = 3`\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add `RepeatedToolFailures` error variant\n\n**Files:**\n- M