\n## Summary\n\nWhen a tool call fails, the agent loop was prematurely terminating instead of allowing the LLM to retry with corrected tool calls in the next iteration. This caused subsequent tool calls in the same response to be skipped entirely.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nIssue from PR #948's `all_failed` early-return: the `break` on tool failure meant only the first tool was attempted, so `all_failed` effectively became \"first tool failed\" → loop exited → LLM never saw the error.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Removed the `all_failed` early return in both streaming and non-streaming code paths in `agent_loop.rs`.\n- Added `consecutive_all_failed` counter that tracks iterations where every executed tool failed with a *hard* error (soft errors — approval denials, sandbox rejections, truncation — do not count).\n- At `MAX_CONSECUTIVE_ALL_FAILED = 3`, loop exits with new `LibreFangError::RepeatedToolFailures { iterations, error_count }`.\n- Kernel's `send_message` Err handler now routes `RepeatedToolFailures` to `push_notification(\"tool_failure\", ...)`, re-wiring the `tool_failure` event that was previously dead.\n- Added 4 regression tests (2 streaming, 2 non-streaming) using mock `LlmDriver` impls to lock in: (a) loop retries after a single tool failure, (b) cap triggers after 3 consecutive all-failed iterations.\n\n## Behavior After Fix\n\n1. **Iteration 0**: tool fails → result saved to session → `consecutive_all_failed=1` → loop continues.\n2. **Iteration 1**: LLM sees error context → retries corrected tool call (resets counter) OR stops with text.\n3. **3 consecutive all-failed iterations**: loop exits with `RepeatedToolFailures`; kernel fires `tool_failure` notification.\n4. `max_iterations=50` remains as a hard ceiling for any other runaway pattern.\n\n## Trade-offs\n\n**Lost:**\n- Immediate error response after a single tool failure (intentional — retry is the whole point).\n\n**Gained:**\n- Proper retry behavior so the LLM can self-correct.\n- Bounded worst-case cost via 